<title>UK: British Aerospace up as McDonnell loses bid.</title>
<headline>British Aerospace up as McDonnell loses bid.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-09-06</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in British Aerospace opened at record for the second consecutive session on news that Australia rejected a bid by McDonnell Douglas to supply T-45 Goshawk aircraft, but retained bids by British Aerospace and Aermacchi SpA, traders said.</p>
<p>By 0738 GMT, British Aerospace shares were up 5p to 1020-1/2p, after rising as high as 1023 at the open.  </p>
<p>Aerospace shares have risen strongly this week as companies dazzled the industry with their latest technological developments the Farnborough air show. 20 percent stake, and Boeing alone announced orders valued at more than $9 billion during the first few days of the show.</p>
<p>&quot;It has been very good for business,&quot; said one British Aerospace market maker.</p>
<p>-- Debra Sherman, London Newsroom +44 171 542 4026</p>
